<TITLE> IGP orders arrest of JnU students who detained officer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 05 (bdnews24.com)- Inspector general of police Nur Muhammad has ordered that the Chhatra League students involved in the detaining of a police officer on Tuesday should be arrested, and a case filed against them. He ordered the additional police commissioner of Dhaka metropolitan to take immediate action about the matter on Wednesday. He was speaking after a three monthly meeting on law and order situation at the police headquarter where he also said that, "Cases will be filed under speedy trial act against those involved in crime, extortion, tender manipulation and crime in the educational institutions." On Tuesday Saidul Islam, a assistant sub-inspector of the Suttrapur Police Station was taken to the Jagannath University campus by Bangladesh Chhatra League activists after he had allegedly assaulted a leader of the student organisation. The police officer wanted to check the papers of the motorcycle that the BCL leader was riding and after a heated argument he had allegedly beaten the student leader. Later it is claimed that 20 to 25 activist of BCL activists led by the president of the organisation Kamrul Hassan Ripon took SI Saiful to the JnU campus and held him in the room of the proctor. He was released after the police promised to take departmental action against the officer. bdnew
